The paper deals with the consistency of data in distributed storage services, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of inversions in a permutation to measure consistency is a technique that is commonly used in database management (cs.DB) and combinatorics (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a verification algorithm, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY).
